border-collapse: collapse: = remove tiny margins and double lines using tables.
margin: 0; = set margin to zero, remove margin for all elements
box-sizing: border-box; = it keep the original size of the box or element when adding padding.

This is how to center content inside element like the div or box.
* {
    margin: 0; /* use this to center the div */
    border-collapse: collapse;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}
table {
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 100%; /* use this to center the div */
}
div {
    margin: 20px; /* use this to center the div */
}

This is for zebra stripe.
tr:nth-child(even) {background-color: #f2f2f2;}

This is for responsive table, an scroll bar on the bottom will add.
<div style="overflow-x: auto;">bord

Use list style type to remove bullets on the links or list
list-style-type: none;

Use max-width instead of width for smaller devices.

Use border-collapse: collapse to remove small space inbetween the table or rows and column.


clearfix hack = use overflow: auto to contain image and text iside element.

if use float

.clearfix::after {
  content: "";
  clear: both;
  display: table;
}

